Description copied from interface: Seekable

Move the internal data pointer to some offset.

The offset should always be one returned by Seekable.position(), e because this interface does not define what the value represents. It could be an array index, or it could be byte offset in a file.

position

public Integer position()
                 throws IOException
Description copied from interface: Seekable

Return the offset of the internal data pointer to the next item that to be read or written.

This value can be used by passing it to Seekable.position(), such that the source will restart from the current position.
